EXPRESSIONS AND STATEMENTS

expressions - is a construct made up of variables, operators, and method invocations, that evaluates to a single value
e.g. 1 + 2 + 3   		returns the value 6
     simpleMethod(1, 2)		returns whatever simpleMethod would return after processing 1 and 2
     "java"			returns the string java

statements - is a unit of execution, so something the compiler executes
e.g. int x = 1 + 2 + 3;
     long x = simpleMethod(1, 2)
     String lang = "java";

types of statements are:
expression statements
declaration statements
control flow statements



